Cosmo First logs 2% rise in Q2 net profit to ₹47 crore
items.author: ETManufacturing Desk
items.summary:
- Cosmo First reports Q2 FY26 PAT of ₹47 crore, up from ₹46 crore, with revenue at ₹919 crore and **EBITDA** ₹128 crore, aided by higher volumes.
- **EBITDA** growth came from a 25% rise in sales volume and the performance of its *specialty chemicals subsidiary*, but margins were pressured by lower BOPP/BOPET film prices, higher US tariffs, and stabilisation costs for new film lines.
- Management expects full utilisation of the new lines by Q4 FY26, with three new products from the *specialty chemicals subsidiary*, and expansion in Zigly and Cosmo Plastech, including an **ESD PET sheet** launch.

items.title: Godavari Biorefineries narrows Q2 FY26 net loss to ₹41.6 crore on 34% revenue growth
GM wants parts makers to pull supply chains from China
Boeing keeps up strong delivery pace in October
items.summary:
- Boeing delivered *53 jets* in October, bringing the year total to *493* as it eyes its highest annual output since 2018. 
- The October mix included *39* of the **737 MAX** (nine to Southwest, five to Ryanair) and *13* widebodies (7 × 787s, 2 × 777 freighters, 4 × 767s). 
- October net orders were *8* after cancellations (15 new orders), with a backlog of *5,911* and regulators approving raising the **737** output to *42 per month*.

items.title: Adani-Cement & Coolbrook to deploy RDH tech in AP plant
items.author: ETManufacturing Desk
items.summary:
- The world’s first commercial *RotoDynamic Heater (RDH)* will be deployed at Adani Cement’s Boyareddypalli plant in Andhra Pradesh to electrify the calcination process.
- The initial phase aims to cut about 60,000 tonnes of CO₂ annually with potential to scale tenfold, advancing **net-zero by 2050** as validated by the **SBTi** and Coolbrook’s CO₂ goals.
- Powered by Adani’s renewable energy, the project delivers **emission-free heat** for decarbonization, supporting higher **AF usage** and a target of 60% green power by FY28.

L&T Technology Services, Autodesk partner to launch AI-led digital manufacturing hub in Vadodara
Can Tenneco Clean Air India’s IPO deliver long term gains for investors?
Thermax Q2 profit drops 40% to ₹119 crore on cost overruns
items.author: ETManufacturing Desk
items.summary:
- **Thermax**'s Q2 consolidated profit fell 40% YoY to ₹119 crore, hit by *project cost overruns* in the *industrial infra* segment.
- Revenue slipped 5% YoY to ₹2,474 crore; **PBT** down 35% to ₹174 crore, with ₹42 crore of additional costs on one project.
- Order balance stood at ₹12,300 crore, up 6%; standalone PAT rose to ₹226 crore aided by ₹141 crore dividend income.

items.title: OECD panel flags excess steel supplies; China exports surge
items.summary:
- **OECD** panel flags excess global steel supplies as **China** exports surge, with worldwide capacity above 680 million tonnes.
- **China** exports have risen about 10% this year and have doubled since 2020-2024 as domestic demand weakens, reshaping global trade.
- **DGTR** of India proposes phased safeguard duties on some flat steel imports (12%, 11.5%, 11%), while industry seeks a 25% barrier to curb China imports.

items.title: India-Russia summit to boost SMRs and localisation
items.author: Dipanjan Roy Chaudhury, ET Bureau
items.summary:
- The 23rd India-Russia summit will push civil nuclear cooperation, including small modular reactors (*SMRs*) and the localisation of nuclear plant equipment.
- Rosatom and India's Department of Atomic Energy discussed expanding large- and small-scale nuclear projects and progress at *KNPP*, with Unit 3 safety testing and Units 4, 5/6 under construction.
- The talks also cover broader cooperation in the *nuclear fuel cycle* and future partnerships beyond KNPP to advance India's nuclear power ambitions.

items.title: Tata Power plans to set up largest solar wafers, ingots making plant
items.summary:
- *Tata Power* plans to build India's largest solar **wafers and ingots** plant with a **10 GW** capacity, tying into its solar manufacturing chain.
- The project would bolster *Tata Power*'s existing **4.9 GW** of integrated cell and module capacity and aligns with India's push to localize wafers/ingots to cut **imports**.
- The company is exploring **federal and state financial support** and will decide total investment in the next two months.

items.title: Centre earmarks ₹100 crore for biomass-to-hydrogen pilots to cut fossil fuel imports
India extends ₹4,000 cr line of credit to Bhutan
items.author: TNN
items.summary:
- India announced a concessional ₹4,000 crore line of credit for Bhutan's energy projects and pledged rail connectivity to Gelephu and Samtse.
- PM Modi and Bhutan's king inaugurated the 1020 MW Punatsangchhu-II hydro project, with a new over-1,000 MW plant boosting Bhutan's capacity by about 40%.
- The two nations signed MoUs on renewable energy, mental health, and healthcare, plus border infrastructure plans and an immigration checkpoint near Gelephu; India also contributed ₹10,000 crore to Bhutan's Five-Year Plan.

items.title: Aim to make India global hub for green hydrogen production: Pralhad Joshi
JSW may sell 50% in Bhushan Power to JFE
Striking Boeing workers to vote Thursday on offer with lower overall bonus
items.summary:
- The more than 3,200 *Boeing Defense* workers on strike will vote Thursday on a new offer that lowers the overall ratification bonus but pays more cash upfront.
- The offer includes a 24% wage increase over five years and a $6,000 upfront bonus if approved (up from $3,000), but cuts $4,000 in later bonuses.
- The strike has delayed F-15 deliveries, and the IAM has accused Boeing of bargaining in bad faith while it hires permanent replacement workers.

items.title: Container Corporation of India Q2 profit edges up 3% to ₹379 crore
items.author: ET Infra Desk
items.summary:
- CONCOR reported consolidated profit attributable to owners of **₹379 crore** for Q2 FY26, up **3.9%** from **₹365 crore** in the year-ago quarter.
- Revenue from operations stood at **₹2,355 crore** in Q2 FY26, nearly flat vs **₹2,288 crore** in Q2 FY25, while total expenses rose to **₹1,945 crore**.
- The board approved a second interim dividend of **₹2.60 per share** for FY26, with the record date of **20 November 2025**.

Tata Power to buy 40% stake in Bhutan hydro SPV
items.summary:
- Tata Power will acquire a 40% equity stake in a Bhutan SPV for approximately **₹1,572 crore** to develop the 1,125 MW *Dorjilung Hydro Power Project*. 
- The SPV will be jointly held by Tata Power and **Druk Green Power Corporation** and the project cost is about **₹13,100 crore**. 
- The deal aims to bolster Tata Power's renewable energy portfolio and accelerate its *clean energy transition*.

items.title: BASF India partners with CleanMax for hybrid solar–wind captive power project in Gujarat
Paras Defence wins ₹35.68cr MoD counter-drone orders
items.author: ETManufacturing Desk
items.summary:
- *Paras Defence* and Space Technologies Ltd. secured two MoD orders worth ₹35.68 crore for *Portable Counter-Drone Systems*, to be delivered by May 2026. 
- Its subsidiary, *Paras Anti-Drone Technologies Pvt. Ltd.*, won an MoD order of ₹3.95 crore for *Radio Frequency jammers*, also due by May 2026. 
- The awards signal growing reliance on **indigenous counter-UAV** capabilities and bolster India’s defence preparedness.

items.title: Jupiter Wagons Q2 net profit falls 49% to ₹45 crore
items.summary:
- *PAT* fell 49% YoY to ₹45.3 crore in Q2 FY26, with a QoQ rise of 46% as wheelset deliveries improved.
- *Total income* at ₹796.1 crore was down 22% YoY but up 67% QoQ, aided by better execution in wagons and components.
- *Wheelset deliveries on track*; order book stood at ₹5,538 crore as of Sep 30, 2025, suggesting smoother operations ahead.

items.title: Delvitech raises $40 mn in Series B round, plans India manufacturing push
Kalyani bags ₹250 crore for underwater systems
items.author: ETManufacturing Desk
items.summary:
- **Kalyani Strategic Systems Ltd (KSSL)**, the defence arm of *Bharat Forge*, won contracts worth over **₹250 crore** from the MoD for underwater systems.
- The deals, signed on 10 November 2025 under **Fast Track Procurement**, require delivery within one year, by November 2026.
- The move underscores a focus on the underwater domain to bolster India's indigenous defence ecosystem and maritime self‑reliance.

items.title: Steep tariffs send air cargo from India to US to 9-year low
items.author: Sunny Baski
items.summary:
- *India–US air cargo* has plunged to a nine‑year low as tariff hikes hit shipments between the two economies.
- DGCA data show Jan–Jun 2025 shipments fell to 4,319 tonnes from 7,152 a year earlier, with handicrafts and other freight hardest hit.
- *Freight forwarders* report demand collapse and exporters cutting orders, while stricter visa norms dampen travel and trade.

items.title: Cheap imports keep pressure on stainless steel prices: Abhyuday Jindal
India's unemployment rate drops to 5.2% amid rural job growth
items.author: ET Bureau
items.summary: - The national unemployment rate dropped to **5.2%** in July-September, driven by rural job gains despite a slight urban rise.\n- Rural unemployment fell to **4.4%** while urban unemployment rose to **6.9%**, showing regional divergence.\n- Labour-force participation rose to **55.1%**, with female participation up to **33.7%**.

items.title: Hindustan Copper Q2 profit up 83% to ₹186 crore
items.author: ETManufacturing Desk
items.summary: - **Hindustan Copper Limited** reported Q2 FY26 net profit of **₹186.02 crore**, up **83%** YoY, driven by stronger operational performance.\n- Revenue from operations rose to **₹718.04 crore** and total income to **₹728.95 crore** in the quarter.\n- For the half-year ended 30 September 2025, **net profit** was **₹320.30 crore**, vs **₹215.07 crore** in the prior half-year.

items.title: India to train 5.7M mining workers by 2030
items.author: Yogima Seth Sharma, ET Bureau
items.summary:
- The government aims to train *5.7 million* skilled workers in mining by 2030 to boost indigenous production of *critical minerals* for *clean energy* and cut imports.
- The *Mines Ministry* and the *Skill Council for Mining Sector* (SCMS) have formed a steering committee to run a 2025–30 skills-gap study under the *National Critical Mineral Mission* (NCMM).
- The plan seeks to lift mining's GDP share from 2.2% to 5% by 2030, building a future-ready, high-tech workforce with ongoing monitoring and a March 2026 recommendations deadline.

items.title: Britannia: Varun Berry resigns as MD, CEO
items.summary:
- Britannia's **MD & CEO Varun Berry** resigns after 13 years, with **Rakshit Hargave** to take over as both MD and CEO.
- Berry had been re-designated as **CEO** in May after Rajneet Kohli's resignation and previously served as Executive Vice-Chairman and MD since joining Britannia in 2013.
- Hargave will assume the role on **December 15** for a five-year term, while insider **Natarajan Venkataraman** is appointed interim CEO.

items.title: Collins Aerospace opens Bengaluru facility with $100M
items.summary:
- RTX's *Collins Aerospace* opens a Bengaluru facility with a **$100M** investment to manufacture advanced aerospace products.
- The 26-acre CIOC at *KIADB Aerospace Park* will employ **2,200+** people by 2026 and produce seats, lighting, cargo systems, sensors and more.
- The **$100M** is part of RTX's broader **$250M** India plan, with the remainder funding an engineering and test development centre and Pratt & Whitney India, signaling long-term growth.

items.title: SoftBank sells entire Nvidia stake for $5.8 billion
Addverb partners with academics to boost robotics education
items.summary:
- **Centres of Excellence** will be set up in robotics and automation at IITs, NAMTECH and NIIT Neemrana to widen access to *robotics education*. 
- Addverb will supply cobots, AGVs, AMRs, shuttles, and the quadruped *Trakr* to support research, training, and industry-linked projects. 
- The initiative aims to bridge education and industry, expand student R&D and open-source parts of AddverbAI, with early outcomes like IIT Gandhinagar papers at IEEE RAS Humanoids and CoRL.

items.title: Bharat Forge Q2 profit up 23%
items.author: ETManufacturing Desk
items.summary:
- Bharat Forge reported Q2 FY26 consolidated profit attributable to owners of **₹299 crore**, up **23%** YoY.
- Revenue from operations rose **9%** YoY to **₹4,032 crore**, with forgings at **₹3,356 crore** and defence at **₹395 crore**.
- The board approved raising up to **₹2,000 crore** via debt instruments, to be executed by the Investment Committee.

items.title: Sugs Lloyd launches consumer brand VYNA Electric
items.author: ETManufacturing Desk
items.summary:
- *Sugs Lloyd* unveils **VYNA Electric**, a premium, consumer-focused brand entering India's electrical and lighting market with modular switches and lighting solutions.
- Initial range covers LED panels, downlighters, COB spotlights, luminaires, distribution boards, RCCBs/MCBs with USB ports and inverter lighting, designed in India and tested to Indian/global standards for safety and durability.
- VYNA Electric begins operations in Delhi, Haryana, Punjab, UP, Chhattisgarh, Uttarakhand and Rajasthan with showroom/dealer distribution and plans to add small home appliances and fans later.

items.title: FCS bets $250m on India; Pune plant
items.summary:
- The *FCS* venture in India with a $250M investment will set up a Pune plant, creating 1,000+ direct jobs.
- The facility will initially produce 2 million cards (metal & biodegradable) with capacity to scale to 26.7 million annually.
- Pune’s logistics and skilled manpower support scaling of *payment solutions from India* to the world, reinforcing India’s fintech manufacturing hub.

items.title: JSW Energy commissions first green hydrogen plant in Karnataka under PLI scheme
US private equity firm General Atlantic set to acquire 7% of Balaji Wafers for ₹2,500 crore
India to train 5.7M miners by 2030
items.summary:
- *India plans to create a pool of 5.7 million skilled mining workers by 2030 to boost **critical minerals** and curb **imports**.*
- *The NCMM and SCMS under the Mines Ministry will run a 2025–30 **skills gap study** to guide workforce development.*
- *The plan targets mining's share of GDP toward **5%** by 2030 and aims to reduce dependence on **China** for imports.*

items.title: Pugal Solar Park to redefine India’s renewable landscape with 5,000 MWh battery storage: Rohit Gupta, CMD, RRECL
French power solutions firm Socomec plans another factory in India with an investment of $10 mn
items.author: G Balachandar
items.summary:
- Socomec, the French *power solutions* player, plans up to *$10 million* to set up a new *manufacturing facility in India*, likely leased to keep upfront capex low.
- It already runs two Gurgaon factories and is weighing southern and western sites, aiming to raise Make in India from about 50% to around 70% of local sales.
- The focus is on *data centers*, renewables, EV charging, and BESS, with R&D improving efficiency and potential acquisitions in switching and monitoring.

items.title: Lohum opens ₹500 cr RE magnet plant
items.author: ETManufacturing Desk
items.summary:
- *Lohum* opens a ₹500 crore RE magnet plant in Uttar Pradesh with 2,000 t capacity for light and heavy rare earths.
- It aims to meet up to *20%* of India’s magnet demand by 2027, boosting EV, renewables and defence manufacturing.
- The project cuts import dependence and strengthens a domestic supply chain, expanding Lohum’s footprint across nine facilities.
